Taco Villa Inc said it is holding talkswith RepublicBank Corp &lt;RPT> to restructure its loan paymentsand waive some financial convenants on its debt.    It also said it may sell certain assets to repay the bankborrowings, and is holding talks with interested parties. Itexpects to write down some previously acquired assets, but thecompany did not say by how much.    At the end of 1986 it had 11 mln dlrs in bank debtoutstanding with a 1.7 mln dlr payment due May one. It is alsoseeking to extend 1.2 mln dlrs of mortgage payments due thisyear, and is in talks to extend other debt payments.    The company said it previously reported special charges ofnine mln dlrs in the fourth quarter from losses on restaurantclosings, lease termination costs, contract settlements andseverance arrangements.    Since it has not yet decided how to treat the additionalwritedowns and debt, it has delayed its 1986 financialstatement. It said it expects to file an amendment to its form10-K but did not say when the amended filing would be made.    The company said it hoped to resolve its debt problems inthe near future. Reuter&#3;